Our plan is to continue to lean into [adoption through usability](/handbook/product/product-principles/#drive-product-usage) and [discoverability](/handbook/product/product-principles/#discoverability-without-being-annoying) in our core stages of Verify, Package, Release and Configure. This will mean sustained focus on onboarding users and organizations from [SCM, to CI to Deployment](/handbook/product/product-principles/#multi-feature-usage-adoption-journey).

For the Monitor stage, we will pursue our common progression product approach to breadth, namely:
1. Create MVCs which showcase the possibility of new categories in a single-application
1. Leverage the high rate of learning provided by dogfooding to achieve viability
1. Shift focus to awareness and acquisition of viable capabilities by increasing SMAU & GMAU
1. Begin building completeness and tier value as a result of increased SMAU

