#### Rationale
Below is the rationale for why and how we believe we can achieve each goal listed above.

##### Verify Stage Rationale
Expected [exit SMAU for Verify](https://app.periscopedata.com/app/gitlab/781120/Ops-Section-Dashboard?widget=13954532&udv=0) is 1.8M in FY23. Historically we have had 20-25% YoY growth. I'd expect as we introduce new features in Ultimate we would support additional growth in the enterprise segment supporting a higher YoY growth in FY24. Our current projected forecast is 2M, with the addition of the CI/CD Catalog, additional Runner Fleet features, and visibility controls for CI/CD Consumption a 16% growth YoY is too small. With the release of GitLab Dedicated and macOS Runner support, I also anticipate greater growth in our SaaS segment. 

##### Package Stage Rationale
Based on the Projected Forcast, in addition to releasing key features of virtual registries, Dependency Firewall, and Instance-level usage data we are anticipating this growth in FY24. With regard to PSMAU, since the virtual registries will mainly focus on Package, I'm taking 18% of 210k (the January 2024 projection) and increasing it by an additional 25% to account for a new market that we will introduce by having greater feature parity with Artifactory.

##### Release Stage Rationale
Estimate an aggressive target of 60% growth each year for SMAU. Growth would come from increased usage from existing customers, enhancing our Environment Management and Release Orchestration capabilities (and better feature parity with / differentiation against competitor tools), instrumentation, and restarting our Feature Flags offering. Another way to approach the target is to look at Release SMAU as a percentage of Verify SMAU (currently 28%) and set a target for this to increase rate of organic growth. We believe we can increase this % to 40%.

##### Configure Stage Rationale
Estimates an SMAU of 312k is a 300% increase YoY from the [FY23 SMAU forecast](https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1U4nHovtwqqf9hW4X1b-8eH3l2rAUVWviF7VojKpCiLc/edit#gid=326559021) of 104k. The PSMAU is estimated to be 60% of SMAU as Kubernetes is likely used mostly by Premium users and we aim to position multi-tenant features to Premium. We plan to reach these goals by improving both the CI/CD and the GitOps flows for the GitLab agent for Kubernetes, by adding observability integrations and by simplifying complex deployments for the developers.

##### Monitor:Respond Rationale
By end of FY24, we expect to have a [complete incident management and on-call management solution](/direction/monitor/debugging_and_health/incident_management/#strategy) that are increasingly lovable. We expect that the complete incident solution is useful to a large portion of the GitLab namespaces/instances because many companies still use DIY solutions for responding to incidents. Our goal is to triple our GMAU by the end of FY23 (50k) and double our GMAU again by the end of FY24 (100k). We believe this aggressive goal is possible because we are confident that our focus on establishing Incidents as SSOT is something that all GitLab users need. Once we can complete the incident management loop via the [planned Slack integration](https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/gitlab-design/-/issues/1944), and eventually paging via SMS or call services, we can see the GMAU really takeoff.

This target is relatively low compared to other stage goals such as Verify or Create. The primary reason for this is the number of users that will interact with incidents is fewer, yet these interactions are for the benefit of the entire organization. We don't expect to build incident management in such a way to enable more people to participate. That said, there may be additional ways to understand the adoption, such as measuring the number of people that are participating in future on-call rotations.

